title: Fulham v Tottenham, FA Cup LIVE score | Daily Mail Online
text:
— Tottenham Hotspur (@SpursOfficial) February 19, 2017 12:58 Meanwhile Tottenham Hotspur have arrived at Craven Cottage...sadly not by boat The team have arrived at Craven Cottage. @Dele_Alli , @ChrisEriksen8 , @HarryWinks and co head into the changing room. #COYS pic.twitter.com/r7PVBO23HM — Tottenham Hotspur (@SpursOfficial) February 19, 2017 12:57 From Sportsmail's Kieran Gill at Craven Cottage 
'A short trip across London for Tottenham, who will hope to get a chance to watch 16-year-old Ryan Sessegnon today. As will the fans watching at home. 
'This kid has attracted interested from the biggest clubs in the world, including both Manchester clubs, Arsenal, Chelsea, Bayern Munich and RB Leipzig. 
'He's scored in Fulham's last two FA Cup ties. XIs coming up so we'll soon see if he starts. ' 12:55 Meanwhile Tottenham fans skip the traffic and arrive on a boat 
Craven Cottage being on the bank of the River Thames, why not take advantage of a boat if it's available? Although they could have renamed the boat King Ledley couldn't they? Tottenham Hotspur fans arrive on a boat for the FA Cup fifth round clash at Craven Cottage Spurs fans will be hoping their side can reach the quarter-finals of the FA Cup 12:49 A sharply dressed Fulham arrive at Craven Cottage The team have arrived, looking sharp in their @PaulSmithDesign suits. ⚫️⚪️ #FFC pic.twitter.com/Gd7SM3oSQz — Fulham Football Club (@FulhamFC) February 19, 2017 12:41 Here are all the results so far from the FA Cup fifth round 
Aside from today's Craven Cottage clash, there are still two other ties to be played including Blackburn Rovers v Manchester United later on as well as non-league Sutton United's huge game at home to Arsenal on Monday. Both of which you can follow live with Sportsmail. 
Click here for more fixtures, tables and results with our excellent Match Zone 12:36 None of the Premier League teams have had it easy so far in the FA Cup fifth round 
Granted, it still didn't stop the likes of Middlesbrough and Chelsea progressing on Saturday but it does provide a hint that we could see a cup shock this afternoon. 
First up it's Fulham against Tottenham and given the form the visitors are in would you bet against the Championship side this afternoon? 
Good afternoon all and welcome to Sportsmail's live coverage of the FA Cup fifth round action from Craven Cottage.
